          {
            "commit": "1951f4dcd29dc7fac74b435c3fb84cb6a95328e7",
            "subject": "LU-13264 osc: ensure lu_ref work atomic from osc_lock_upcall()"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Wang Shilong",
          "email": "wshilong@ddn.com",
          "date": "2020-02-29 04:47:14.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Wang Shilong",
          "email": "wshilong@ddn.com",
          "date": "2020-02-29 05:31:26.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-13312 llite: improve RA under memory pressure",
        "message": "LU-13312 llite: improve RA under memory pressure\n\nCurrently, readahead pages won't try memory reclaim from FS if\nmemory filled up, this is used to avoid discarding pages, as\nLustre use RA aggressively.\n\nBut this could cause another problem with RA under pressure,\nA lot of small read happen because of RA could be proceed,\nhowever, we should at least try memory reclaim to cover current\nread range, as this is indeed needed and reclaim will happen\nlater anyway.\n\nThis patch make a balanced value, with first one RPC size, we\ntry to memory reclaim, otherwise, we stop readahead.\n\nChange-Id: I8356b13c0d5e807ea1171f35e3c9e27035ba8f2d\nSigned-off-by: Wang Shilong <wshilong@ddn.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
